^C2f THE LOST MUTANTS - MISSION

^C2d STORY

^C00 While Dr Goldfire has been on the run since taking out his operations, a senior scientist of russian descent from his corporation (Serge Ivankov) has been setting up Mutant Operations in the Scandinavian Mountains.

^P
^C2f THE LOST MUTANTS - MISSION

^C2d STORY

^G62,17,10
^C00 Intelligence pinpoints the co-ordinates and presents Blake Stone with the co-ordinates. Ivankov is producing new mutants as part of Goldfire's sinister plan to enslave humanity.

^P
^C2f THE LOST MUTANTS - MISSION

^C2d STORY

^C00 Serge Ivankov is creating his own reign of mutants, much like that of Dr Goldfire, using the material and assets provided by Goldfire.  It is said that many STAR military are also deployed with Ivankov.

^C00 Acknowledging Intelligence, you fly off to the Scandinavian mountains. Cloudy and with grey skies coming, you battle thunder and lightning until some time later you take down on the ground nearby.

^P
^C2f THE LOST MUTANTS - MISSION

^C2d STORY

^C00 These creations are no toy or reason to mess with. These are killing machines who can be experiments gone wrong, hence the deaths of many bio technicians in Dr Goldfire's institute.

^P
^C2f THE LOST MUTANTS - MISSION

^C2d STORY

^C00 Analysis reports of Ivankov's hideout determines a generator somewhere is also being used to help power these lost mutants he's creating on behalf of Dr Goldfire. Ferocious beasts, modified soldiers, cyborg guards and nuisance creatures await.

^P
^C2f THE LOST MUTANTS - MISSION

^C2d STORY

^C00 Ivankov is a phd educated scientist who joined STAR and has worked his way up, using his high IQ to become a sidekick to Dr Goldfire. Goldfire has equipped him. Take it easy as you won't be familiar with how he operates.

^P
^C2f THE LOST MUTANTS - MISSION

^C2d STORY

^C00 Taking down on the ground in the mountainside, you hurrry your way to see an installation ahead, tired but weary, and taking your weapon, you sneak to the Ground Ops in front of you, ready to infiltrate and discover and destroy the Lost Mutants!

^P
^C2f THE LOST MUTANTS - MISSION

^C2d FEATURES

^C00 - Seamless level flow
- 25 Levels including a secret level
- 6 weapons in total
- 4 keys in total
- New enemies
- New code changes
- New Helpart, & Endart
- New Music, sounds, graphics etc
- 200 Ammo

^P
^C2f THE LOST MUTANTS - MANUAL

^C2d PLAYING THE GAME - WEAPONS/AMMUNITION

^C00 During your mission you'll be using 6 different weapons, starting with the stun-gun and slow-fire protector. You can obtain the Rapid assault rifle, Duel neutron disruptor, Plasma charge unit and Flamethrower. Once you've received all these weapons you can choose any weapon by choosing the numbers 1-6. Pressing ^C27 1 ^C00 Stun Gun, ^C27 2 ^C00 Slow Fire Protector, ^C27 3 ^C00 Rapid Assault Rifle, ^C27 4 ^C00 Dual Neutron Disruptor, ^C27 5 ^C00 Plasma Charge Unit, ^C27 6 ^C00 Flamethrower.

^P
^C2f THE LOST MUTANTS - MANUAL
^G50,16,15

^C2d PLAYING THE GAME - WEAPONS/AMMUNITION

^C00 In your mission you'll be encounter 2 ammo pick ups, i.e small charge packs and large charge packs, of which you'll be able to carry and then provided you have all 6 weapons, you're in good hands.
The charge units are suitable for the Slow Fire Protector, Rapid Assault Rifle, Dual Neutron Disruptor, Plasma Discharge Unit and Flamethrower.
^P
^C2f THE LOST MUTANTS - MANUAL
^G50,16,9

^C2d PLAYING THE GAME - WEAPONS/AMMUNITION

^C00 The slow-fire protector is useful when encountering single guards, while the Rapid Assault Rifle and Dual Neutron Disruptor are useful for taking big groups of guards. The Disruptor is best used when encounting a large group of guards or even against the bigger enemies you will encounter.
^P
^C2f THE LOST MUTANTS - MANUAL
^G50,16,16

^C2d PLAYING THE GAME - WEAPONS/AMMUNITION

^C00 The Plasma Discharge Unit is useful for dealing with tougher enemies and the Flamethrower is scarce but great for difficult combat.
^P
^C2f THE LOST MUTANTS - MANUAL
^G50,16,16
^G100,16,15

^C2d PLAYING THE GAME - WEAPONS/AMMUNITION

^C00 The Plasma Discharge Unit can be found ocasionally in secret areas.

^C00 The Flamethrower fires flames at enemies. In later missions, it will be very useful if found.

^P
