^C2d PLAYING THE GAME - ENEMIES

^C00 There is several different enemy types you may encounter through out the game, some of which will drop charge packs killed. They can be human, robot or mutant.

^P
^C2f THE LOST MUTANTS - MANUAL
^G55,19,4

^C2d PLAYING THE GAME - ENEMIES

^C27 1. Bio Technicians: ^C00 Poor in combat but skilled in operations for STAR. Don't expect them to be friendly. Fire back if they fire at you.

^P
^C2f THE LOST MUTANTS - MANUAL
^G55,19,4

^C2d PLAYING THE GAME - ENEMIES

^C27 2. Plasma Sphere: ^C00 Very annoying and flying around each station. Even bio technicians see them as a nuisance. Take them out to avoid nuisance attacks.

^P
^C2f THE LOST MUTANTS - MANUAL
^G55,19,4

^C2d PLAYING THE GAME - ENEMIES

^C27 3. Sentinel: ^C00 The solid military of STAR. They are equipped with the Rapid Assault Rifle and shoot on site any intruder. Be careful!

^P
^C2f THE LOST MUTANTS - MANUAL
^G55,19,4

^C2d PLAYING THE GAME - ENEMIES

^C27 4. Mutant Bat: ^C00 Captured and enslaved, Serge Ivankov had the bio techs perform cruel modifications to them. Now they are killers, even against their makers.
^P
^C2f THE LOST MUTANTS - MANUAL
^G55,19,4

^C2d PLAYING THE GAME - ENEMIES

^C27 5. Sector Patrol: ^C00 These guards patrol the bases in the game and are much tougher than a Bio Technician. They are dangerous in packs so watch your back.
^P
